values:
I don't have much time to write today. I'm updating my journal from a friends house, while currently my computer at home is being fixed. There's actually nother wrong with it, it's just that when we installed Windows XP, we had to install all our regular programs in again, including Norton AntiVirus systems. We misplaced the installation disk, unfortunantly.. ^^;; Now we have to find it, or surfing the internet will burden all of us with the pain of pop-ups. 

Yesterday I was absent from school because of a bug going around. -_- I layed in bed almost all day and slept. My fever was around 102.3 Degrees.. now it's around 99.7 Degrees. My mom forced me to go to school today, even with this massive headache. Hopefully the Motrin Jade gave me will help it go away. Speaking of Jade, she's behind me watching. The whole time. o_o;;

Anyways, I'll update later.

The past days have come by pretty smoothly. Thursday was take your son/daughter to work day, which I participated in fully. I went with my mom's boyfriend to his work. He works as the delivery manager of Home Depot, and it was pretty neat. We wore aprons around the store, a couple people even asked us (my sister and I) if we worked there. We got to keep the aprons, and went home after a couple of hours. On the way home after I raised enough money for it, I finally bought the Liger Zero Schneider. This thing comes with both the Zero and the Schneider armor, which actually surprised me. I thought it would only be the Schneider. 

     Our Geography Teacher's mother died today, and she wasn't in school. I feel very sorry for her.. it reminds me of when I lost my best friend Jamie, when I was only a kid. I wrote a sympathy letter to her, and hopefully it will lift her spirits to know somebody cares about what has happened.

     Other than that life is good now. Tommorow morning I have to go to my future High School, Fairmont, for a band competition. I'm playing in a percussion trio, and I'm playing a solo on the Snare Drum. I don't like getting up early on weekends, it makes no sense.. but I have to be there by 9 o'clock. Yay.. -_-;
